    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>General term for the cultures and styles, regardless of period, of the westernmost protrusion of Asia, which makes up the majority of the modern Republic of Turkey. To refer to the ancient cultures of this region, use "Anatolian," although there is overlap in usage. To distinguish the nationality of the modern nation of Turkey, use "Turkish."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
